result.name: 稻庭養助

reviews.text: Plenty of choices for the lunch menu. The fried oysters were fresh and juicy. It was the best to have the chicken soup that made you warm and comforting in the rainy day. The hamburg steak was not salty and its sauce really brought up the appetite.

Lunch hour and only half the seats were occupied. We were nonetheless asked to wait in the very crowded lift lobby. 10 minutes later, the lift lobby was packed, the restaurant still half empty. The waiter just rudely shooed us off and walked away.

Have eaten here before. Reasonable lunch set.

Not worth the abuse and not coming back.
Authentic Japanese restaurant, portions are a bit small but a definite good place to hang out and eat
Minus one star for no free water.(even they have free tea)

Lunch set choices were abundant! Each of them consisted of a number of Japanese delicacy! Ingredients were impressively fresh and food was finely seasoned! Staff members were efficient and friendly and in fact, if you were to be assigned to the bar seat, you could observe and be amazed by how regimented the work flow in the kitchen was! One minor complaint - the ventilation system was disappointing and my clothes reeked after the meal!
